description: Number of terms on the n-th level of the Inverse-Totient-Tree (ITT). The 0th, 1st, 2nd and 3rd levels are {1}, {2}, {3, 4, 6}, {5, 7, 8, 9, 10, 12, 14, 18} with 1, 1, 3, 8 entries resp. The (n+1)-st level is obtained from the n-th level as the union of the inverse phi sets of the terms occurring earlier on the n-th level.
